Part One is here: https://patriots.win/p/199Ohyylxl/election-night-magathread--fight/c

We are also expecting President Trump to address people sometime in the next hour or so. His victory party is watching the news live and waiting for these states to be called. Kamala's campaigned has already announced that this won't be resolved tonight.

posts.content:
This thread is for information only. Please see the homepage for the latest MAGAthread.

Tonight's MAGAthreads

  • Part 1 - FIGHT FIGHT FIGHT
  • Part 2 - LEANING TRUMP
  • Part 3 - WAITING FOR GEOTUS

Streaming Coverage

  • ABC News / 538
  • Fake News CNN
  • Failing New York Times

News Feeds

  • Rich Baris - X
  • Decision Desk HQ - X

Schedule for Tonight

6:00 PM - The first polls will close in the Eastern Time portions of Indiana and Kentucky. This is when election night officially starts, but there won't be any interesting results this early.

7:00 PM - Indiana and Kentucky will both be called immediately when their polls close at 7 PM. South Carolina being called immediately would be the first good sign, but it's not a problem if they wait for the first results to come in first. Vermont not being called immediately for Harris would also be a good sign that the networks are unsure how well Trump will do based on the exit polling alone. Georgia and Virginia also close here, but it will take a couple hours for enough results to come in. Most of Florida closes as well, but nobody will call the state until the polling places in the panhandle close.

7:30 PM - North Carolina, Ohio, and West Virginia close. West Virginia will be called immediately. Ohio being called immediately would be a good sign. North Carolina being called immediately could indicate a Trump landslide is imminent. Don't fret if they aren't however, as the networks have become much more cautious in the last couple elections. Election desks may want to see at least some actual results first.

8:00 PM - A whole slew of states close here. Immediately called for Trump: Alabama, Mississippi, Oklahoma, Tennessee. Immediately called for Harris: Connecticut, Delaware, Illinois, Maryland, Massachusetts, Rhode Island, Washington DC. If any of these states aren't called immediately, that's another indicator of the way the night is going. The rest of Florida closes and it may be called immediately based on results from the rest of the state. Additionally, Maine, New Hampshire, and Pennsylvania will close and not be called. Also, Missouri and New Jersey are early indicators. Listen to what they say about these states. Missouri should go for Trump and New Jersey for Harris, but I expect neither to be called immediately.

8:30 PM - Arkansas closes and is called for Trump. Keep an eye on Virginia. If Trump wins Virginia, it's the best sign we have that Trump is going to win the election. We'll be watching results come in from North Carolina and Ohio, wondering how much more we need to see before they call these states. If Florida wasn't called immediately, we will be looking at results there as well. Also, Rhode Island is a state where Trump polled well and will have results coming in fast.

9:00 PM - Immediately called for Trump: Kansas, Louisiana, Nebraska (minus one district), North Dakota, South Dakota, Wyoming. Immediately called for Harris: New York (could be big if not). Other states closing: Arizona, Colorado, Iowa, Michigan, Minnesota, New Mexico, Texas, Wisconsin. Much of Texas closed an hour earlier, and it would be a good sign if it was called immediately. Results from Georgia should be coming in now, and this is a state that Trump really needs to win. Either Ohio will be called for Trump or we're going to be wondering why they're not calling it based on the results we're seeing. If Ohio is close, we're in trouble.

10:00 PM - Immediately called for Trump: Montana and Utah. Nevada also closes. Colorado should be coming in, and this is another state that Trump should win if there's a landslide. Texas should be called for Trump now. We'll be watching for an Iowa call, which is another state that Trump needs to win. We're going to start to see Wisconsin data and some data from Michigan - these are two states which Harris needs to win. We'll also be watching Pennsylvania. Hopefully we have won North Carolina and Georgia by now, and this state would be the third and final Trump key to victory.

10:30 PM - This is about the earliest that we'll know that Trump has won the election. Look for these signs of a big night: Trump has won Virginia. Trump is looking good in Wisconsin, Pennsylvania, and Arizona. Trump is competitive in Colorado, New Mexico, and Maine. New Jersey and/or Rhode Island still haven't been called. Trump has won New Hampshire.

11:00 PM - Idaho should be immediately called for Trump and California for Harris. Maybe Washington for Harris, too, but Oregon, probably not. Keep an eye on Colorado, Minnesota, and New Mexico. These are states that Harris is going to need in order to win, but they will be competitive is Trump is having a good night. At this point, we should be looking at Pennsylvania being called for Trump. Together with Georgia and North Carolina, this should give Trump the win, although they may not call it yet.

11:30 PM - Before they can call the election, Trump will have to get to 270 projected electoral votes. With all the states that should be called by now, adding Pennsylvania only gives him 267. He will need one more state, likely from this list: Virginia, Wisconsin, Michigan, Arizona, Nevada, New Hampshire, Colorado, New Mexico, Minnesota, New Jersey, Rhode Island.

12:00 AM - Alaska and Hawaii both close. Alaska probably won't get called immediately, but Hawaii will go to Harris. If none of the other swing states have come in, Alaska will put Trump over the top, but results typically come in very slowly.
